    <item>
      <title>Version 1.0.0-beta1</title>
      <pubDate>Fri, 06 Feb 2026 16:37:16 +0000</pubDate>
      <sparkle:version>1.0.0.1</sparkle:version>
      <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.0.0-beta1</sparkle:shortVersionString>
      <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>13.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
      <description><![CDATA[
        <h2>What's New in 1.0.0-beta1</h2>
        <p>Initial beta release of Intake — a minimalist macOS menu bar utility for capturing thoughts and routing them anywhere.</p>
        <h3>Capture</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Global hotkey</strong> — Summon the capture panel instantly from any app</li>
          <li><strong>Smart panel</strong> — Auto-focuses the title field; resizes dynamically</li>
          <li><strong>Offline queue</strong> — Captures auto-retry when connectivity returns</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>Destinations</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Built-in adapters</strong> — URL scheme, AppleScript, file, and webhook</li>
          <li><strong>Todoist, Raindrop.io, Pocket, Pinboard</strong> — Direct integrations</li>
        </ul>
        <h3>History &amp; Data</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Capture log</strong> — Browse, filter, export, and delete past captures</li>
          <li><strong>iCloud sync</strong> — Settings sync across your Macs</li>
          <li><strong>Secure storage</strong> — API keys stored in macOS Keychain</li>
        </ul>
      ]]></description>
